107
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:10,835
[Bass Crooning]

108
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:17,957
- I love you too
- [Crooning]

109
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:22,596
- [Chuckling]
- "Paz-a-muh-quoddy."

110
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:26,076
Passamaquoddy.
Sounds like a nice place.

111
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,397
[Mumbling Gibberish]

112
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:33,718
Now, Elliott, we want the people
of Passamaquoddy to like us.

113
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:37,071
- Don't we?
- [Gibberish]

114
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:40,988
I mean, you're kind of big,
and we don't want to scare anyone.

115
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:46,274
- Do we?
- [Growling, Clicking Tongue]

116
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:49,153
So you better not
show yourself, understand?

117
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:52,113
[Gasps, Sighs]

118
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:55,550
I know how ya feel, but you'll
have to make yourself invisible.

119
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:00,557
[Humming]

120
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,268
Nope.

121
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:11,117
- [Panting]
- Uh-uh.

122
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:20,438
- Nope. [Giggling]
- [Gibberish]

123
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:26,317
- Nope.
- [Moaning]

124
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:32,552
- [Panting]
- I'm sorry, but
the whole thing has to go.

125
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:40,990
Behave yourself, Elliott.

126
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:45,519
[Elliott Muttering]

127
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,437
[Muttering Continues]

128
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:52,949
[Meowing]

129
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,791
[Sighs]

130
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,835
- Hi!
- [Clattering]

131
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:22,314
- [Whinnying]
- [Shouting]

132
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,871
I told ya
not to fool around.

133
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,195
Get on the sidewalk
and stay next to me.

134
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:38,797
[Banging]

135
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:45,236
[Squishing]

136
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,236
Look out, Elliott!

137
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:03,230
- Oops. Clumsy, clumsy, clumsy.
- [All Laughing]

138
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,510
I'm sorry, real sorry.

139
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:08,552
I was telling my dragon
not to bump his head on the sign.

140
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:15,270
All right, smarties.
Into your classroom.

141
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,470
March, march, march
march, march!

142
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,994
[Teacher]
March! March!

143
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,475
March! March!

144
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,477
How dare you?

145
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,910
I mean, how dare you lie and try
to embarrass me in front of my students.

146
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:34,077
- I wasn't lying.
- That's a lie on top of a lie.

147
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:37,875
Ugh! You're not
one of my pupils.

148
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,877
What school are you
playing hooky from?

149
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,551
- I-I don't go to school.
- Ah! I knew it.

150
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,557
That's just
what this town needs.

151
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:49,399
- [Elliott Giggling]
- [Teacher] Another ignoramus.

152
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:52,796
- No, Elliott.
- [Ripping]

153
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:55,354
[All Laughing]

154
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:58,711
You disgusting
little street urchin!

155
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:03,596
You could be locked up for this.
Where's the sheriff?

156
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:06,632
Gentlemen,
I propose to say...

157
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:09,513
Passamaquoddy's
a beautiful community...

158
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:14,077
where the sun always rises
and the sun always sets.

159
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,713
- That's very deep.
- Elliott...

160
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,195
It's a place of serenity
and security,

161
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:21,995
where the unexpected
never happens.

162
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,997
- Ow!
- [Elliott Grumbles, Growls]

163
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:26,998
- It's okay, Elliott.
- [Astonished Mumbling]

164
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,951
It seems to say,
"Welcome!"

165
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,992
You-You absolute oaf.

166
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,873
You-You idiot!

167
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,719
- No, come, come.
- Look, it was that kid that pushed me.

168
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,274
He pulled off
Miss Taylor's petticoat.

169
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:47,154
- He walked through my cement
with his big feet.
- He scared my horse, Victoria.

170
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,555
Let's get out
of here, Elliott.

171
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:53,559
- We-Well, where is this person?
- Th-There he goes!

172
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:56,638
- Well, detain him. Detain him.
- [Crowd Shouting]

173
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,671
[Chuckling]

174
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:13,678
- Elliott...
- Uh-oh.

175
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,473
- You spoiled everything.
- [Gibberish]

176
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,160
Darn you, Elliott.

177
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:24,956
I told you to behave.

178
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,799
[Sorrowful Gibberish]

179
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,876
[Sighs]

180
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:50,632
Scallops.
And some oysters.

181
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,751
And...

182
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:55,792
Oh, hello there,
little boy.

183
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:59,708
- Hi.
- [Sniffing]

184
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:04,833
- Hi.
- [Puzzled Gibberish]

185
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:09,988
- Hey! Hey, you look terrible.
- Whoopee!

186
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:15,592
Hey, your friend's...
turned green.

187
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:20,794
- [Gibberish]
- If I didn't know any better,

188
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,195
I'd say he was a dragon.

189
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:27,279
- A drag-drag...
- [Growls]

190
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:30,429
Dragon!

191
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:34,991
- Elliott, didn't I tell you that...
- [Frantic Gibberish]

192
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:39,113
- [Loud Chattering]
- [Screaming, Indistinct]

193
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,877
[Gibberish]

194
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:51,959
Oh! Gentlemen...

195
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:55,595
A dragon, a dragon
I swear I saw a dragon

196
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:58,757
A green and seething
fire-breathing monster is in sight

197
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:02,156
With eyes of red a lion's head
and wings as dark as night

198
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:05,750
Oh, he has a jaw of gleaming teeth
He's 50 feet in height

199
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:09,236
It's true, it's true
Oh, what are we to do

200
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:12,670
It's true, it's true
He'll break us all in two

201
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:17,032
Oh, he's comin' in
His great big fin
is right against the door

202
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:19,799
So board up all the windows

203
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:23,833
And get down on the floor

204
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,997
Has anybody seen my dad?

205
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:30,954
Nora, please,
my child, come in.

206
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:33,435
- Get off that street.
- What's the matter?

207
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:36,393
- Worst thing I ever saw
in my life out on the street.
- What was it?

208
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:40,069
- I don't want to tell you for
fear it'll scare you to death!
- Scare me.

209
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:43,795
A dragon, a dragon
I swear I saw a dragon

210
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:47,595
His tail lashing, he'll be
smashing every shop in town

211
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:50,871
With scaly feet he'll crack the street
and tear the steeple down

212
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,549
It's not some loony dream
I heard a scream from Sheriff Brown

213
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:57,877
It's true, it's true
Oh, what are we to do

214
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:01,310
- It's true, it's true
- Old Lampie's in a stew

215
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:05,149
A dragon, a dragon
I swear there was a dragon

216
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:08,556
You're off your hinges
All those binges put you in a haze

217
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:11,990
You crazy fools
It's all your doggone fault
he's in a daze

218
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:16,398
Let go of me, let go of me
and mend your wicked ways

219
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:19,876
- [Braying]
- Aah!

220
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,195
What makes you think there
ever was, there never was

221
00:19:22,320 --> 00:19:25,357
There never, never, ever was
a dragon, dragon, dragon

222
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:28,517
Dragon, dragon
dragon, dragon, dragon

223
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:33,954
[Grumbling,
Indistinct]

224
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:44,271
- Now, why don't you just calm down?
- I seen his face.

225
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:46,436
If you wanna
call it a face.

226
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,676
It was this close to me.

227
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,030
Why don't you
lie down, Dad? Come on.

228
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:56,632
You know what else?
It started to smile at me.

229
00:19:56,760 --> 00:20:02,153
- Well, did you smile back?
- I didn't have time to smile.
I was too busy running.

230
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:08,593
And you know...
And you know what else?

231
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:11,757
There was this boy with it.

232
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:14,348
And he wasn't afraid.

233
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,472
- This boy...
- Lie down.

234
00:21:25,320 --> 00:21:28,278
[Clicking, Mumbling]

235
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,475
[Gibberish]

236
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:07,071
[Gibberish]

237
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:13,071
[Humming]

238
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:26,877
We're in a lot of trouble,
and it's all your fault.

239
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:39,271
[Sighing]

240
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:53,510
[Inhaling]

241
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,517
[Exhaling]

242
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:03,836
[Inhaling, Exhaling]

243
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:09,431
I don't wanna play.

244
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,590
You did everything wrong
is Passamaquoddy.

245
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,870
Now everybody hates us.

246
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:27,037
I don't know whether
you're good for me...

247
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:29,037
or bad.

248
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:34,197
[Sniffles]

249
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:41,274
I'm sorry, Elliott.
I didn't really mean that.

250
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:44,039
It's just
I don't know what to do,

251
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,151
and I'm scared.

252
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,396
[Sniffles]

253
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:57,040
[Groans]

254
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,836
Hello in there!

255
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:07,076
[Whispering]
Get back!

256
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,156
[Grumbling, Grunting]

257
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:18,638
Hi.

258
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:24,232
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, just playing tic-tac-toe.

259
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:27,511
[Chuckling] Well, this isn't exactly
the best place for tic-tac-toe.

260
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:30,712
The tide's coming in.
High water reaches this cave sometimes.

261
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,717
You better
head for home.

262
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,830
You're not from
Passamaquoddy, are you?

263
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:43,636
Nope.
Just sort of... traveling.

264
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,911
Where are your parents?

265
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:50,557
Where are you staying?

266
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:55,196
- What's your name?
- Pete.

267
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:59,074
I'm Nora, and I have to get back
on watch, up in the lighthouse.

268
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:02,510
There's chowder on the stove,
if you'd like some.

269
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:14,679
Wh-What's the matter?
It's a hand, not a shark.

270
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:19,073
You can finish that chowder...

271
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:23,555
if you'd like.

272
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:35,271
[Exhales, Sniffles]

273
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:40,635
Oh, I forgot something.
Be right back.

274
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:47,471
I forgive you, Elliott.

275
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:53,388
- [Giggles]
- [Sighs, Chuckles]

276
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:02,188
Stay here till I see what
it's like up in the lighthouse.

277
00:26:03,320 --> 00:26:05,515
Woo-woo-woo-woo!

278
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,477
The Gogans own me,
I guess.

279
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,910
They said it was against the law
for me to ever leave them.

280
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:22,037
Where did you get
that bruise?

281
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:25,755
Mr. Gogan. I was milking the cow,
and I missed the bucket.

282
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:30,476
- Had he done that before?
- All the time.

283
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:34,434
The first time I ran away,
the orphan home sent me back.

284
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:37,233
This time,
I'll just keep running.

285
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:41,040
Well, you'll be safe here.

286
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:46,154
Nora, no one's ever been this nice
to me. I'll always remember it.

287
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:48,635
Pete, why don't you
sleep here tonight?

288
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,910
We'll figure out
what to do tomorrow.

289
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:53,474
Okay?

290
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:56,592
Wonderful.
I've got work to do. Come on.

291
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:00,276
Are you anybody's mother?

292
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,516
I'm not even anybody's wife.

293
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:05,837
But you're gonna get
married now, aren't you?

294
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:09,396
[Scoffs] I'm already married
to this lighthouse.

295
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:13,479
- Who's that?
- Paul.

296
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:17,149
- Is he part of your family?
- He almost was.

297
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:21,114
- How can someone almost
be part of a family?
- We were going to be married.

298
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:24,630
How come you weren't?

299
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:29,629
Well, as far as we know,
his ship was headed for a storm.

300
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:34,675
They were never heard from again.
That was a year ago.

301
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:37,678
He'll come back.

302
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,314
I tell myself
the same thing every day,

303
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:44,069
standing up there
watching for ships on the horizon.

304
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:47,636
[Sighs] Time I should be thinking of
other things, so they tell me.

305
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,589
I'll have to ask
Elliott about Paul.

306
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:52,676
He has a way
of knowing things.

307
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:54,677
Who's Elliott?

308
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:57,633
- My dragon.
- Dragon?

309
00:27:57,760 --> 00:28:00,832
[Gasps]
So you're the boy with the dragon.

310
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:03,235
- Yup.
- Where is he?

311
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:06,591
- Down in the cave.
- That's interesting.

312
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:10,315
I've never known anyone with a dragon.
What does he look like?

313
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,670
Just a plain,
ordinary dragon.

314
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,553
How plain?
How ordinary?

315
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:19,070
He has the head of a camel

316
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:21,236
The neck
of a crocodile

317
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:23,749
It sounds rather strange.

318
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:27,156
He's both
a fish and a mammal

319
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:32,718
And I hope
he'll never change

320
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:37,550
'Cause it's not easy
to find someone who cares

321
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:41,673
It's not easy
to find magic in pairs

322
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:44,109
I'm glad I found him
I love him

323
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:48,119
I won't let him
get away

324
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:52,472
'Cause it's not easy

325
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:58,555
You say
the head of a camel

326
00:28:58,680 --> 00:29:02,355
- The neck of a crocodile
- And the ears of a cow!

327
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:06,837
It's clear that friends
can be different

328
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:11,112
Yes, I understand you now

329
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:16,919
[Together] It's not easy
to find someone who cares

330
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:21,158
It's not easy
to find magic in pairs

331
00:29:21,280 --> 00:29:23,714
Now that you have him
Hold him

332
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:27,310
Treasure him
from day to day

333
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:32,118
It's so easy

334
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:38,953
Life is lollipops
and raindrops

335
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:42,959
With the one
you love

336
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:46,595
Someone you can
always be with

337
00:29:46,720 --> 00:29:49,359
Argue and agree with

338
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,753
Climb the highest tree with

339
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:57,554
[Together]
It's not easy

340
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:59,557
To share somebody's dream

341
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:03,753
It gets easy
when you work as a team

342
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:06,394
You've got to tend it
Fan it

343
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:11,036
That's what
I plan to do

344
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:16,393
Oh, I had one friend
by my side

345
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:21,229
Now I have two

346
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:24,272
Him and you

347
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:30,552
Him and me

348
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:35,276
[Together]
And it's so easy

349
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:59,632
[Humming]

350
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:20,836
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning, son.

351
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:24,794
- Nice to see you again.
- Ah. Thank you.

352
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:28,350
Aah!

353
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:31,790
- It's you!
- What's the matter?

354
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:35,071
It's you.
The boy with the dragon.

355
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:37,236
Yes, sir.

356
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:41,797
[Screaming]

357
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:44,480
Dad! Dad, what is it?

358
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:49,628
- The boy with the dragon.
- I know, I know. Now, just take it easy.

359
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:51,910
You saw it.
You saw it?

360
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,395
I didn't actually see it,
but I know what it looks like.

361
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:57,398
- But wha...
- We'll talk about it later.

362
00:31:57,520 --> 00:32:02,196
O-One thing I must know:
It isn't in the lighthouse, is it?

363
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:05,596
- No, Elliott's down in the cave.
- Oh, Ellio...

364
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:10,236
Elliott? Lt... It even has a name.

365
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,874
There's nothing
to get upset about.

366
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,958
You're right. Right, there's
nothing to get upset about.

367
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:18,514
Nothing. No, why should I get upset?
I should be happy.

368
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:23,316
L... I should be happy! I'll go down
to the saloon and I'll tell the boys.

369
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:27,831
I'll say, "Boys, here it is."
And then hear the apologies. [Laughs]

370
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:31,396
Elliott'll be happy
to do it for you, sir.

371
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,670
Good boy. Good lad.

372
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,519
Just you and me and Elliott.
We'll go into the saloon.

373
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:38,756
Oh. Elliott...

374
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:41,075
He won't... won't start
to scratch or...

375
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:43,555
or fight, or set anything
on fire, will he?

376
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:46,592
- Well, he's sort of...
- Sort of what?

377
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:50,474
- Unpredictable.
- Now, don't do anything with Elliott.

378
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:52,477
Wh-Why don't you
leave him where he is?

379
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:55,876
- It's too dangerous
to take him into town.
- It's dangerous.

380
00:32:56,000 --> 00:32:59,276
Now, I don't want either one of you
to say a word about Elliott...

381
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,277
- to anyone, do you understand,
- No. No. Yes!

382
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:03,356
Until we've
talked this over.

383
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:06,438
Now, let's all have breakfast. The lamp
has to be polished, the lens cleaned,

384
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:08,437
and I want to take Pete
to buy new clothes.

385
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:10,437
Yes, well, clean Elliott
and eat the lamp.

386
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:12,790
I mean, we'll...
clea-clean the lamp.

387
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:16,833
[Muttering] Elliott!
The name's Elliott. Did you hear that?

388
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:28,595
Doc Terminus is comin'!

389
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:39,637
Are they still after us?

390
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,716
We lost 'em.

391
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:44,035
Good.

392
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:49,275
- Passamaquoddy ahead, ahoy!
- What?

393
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:53,678
Pass-a-ma-quoddy ahead, ahoy!

394
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:56,792
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yes.

395
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:05,593
[Dog Barking]

396
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:12,029
- [Screams] Slow down!
- My fence!

397
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,996
Throw out the anchor!

398
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:23,477
Since we all concur, gentlemen,
I suggest that we adjourn.

399
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:25,477
[Screams]

400
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:27,989
[Townspeople Screaming]

401
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:40,193
- Watch Bones.
- Get him off of me! Get him off!

402
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,118
I think they remember us.

403
00:34:46,240 --> 00:34:48,913
Uh-oh. I think
I remember them.

404
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:53,113
- Just act normal.
- I am acting normal. I'm ready to run.

405
00:34:53,240 --> 00:34:57,119
- Quick, what's the name
of this town again?
- Passamaquoddy.

406
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:59,595
- "Quassama" what?
- Passamaquoddy!

407
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:03,599
Got it. How wonderful to see
your smiling faces again.

408
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,870
All of you.

409
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,956
I-I've never known
such warmth,

410
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,957
such welcome,

411
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:12,435
such loving hospitality.

412
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:15,438
Get out, ya quack!

413
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,551
And don't bring those
phony remedies here again.

414
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,989
Go on back where
you belong: Jail.

415
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:24,318
- [Booing]
- Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you.

416
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:26,351
I sense enthusiasm,

417
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:28,436
I sense loving response,

418
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,757
and that's why I feel
that this is my home...

419
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,030
away from home.

420
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:37,516
I've been bringing cures
from Pilgrim Heights to Provincetown

421
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:40,712
Treated rabid fever
down on Queen Anne Road

422
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:44,435
Gout or gastritis
Mumps or bronchitis

423
00:35:44,560 --> 00:35:48,235
Bites and burns and blue abrasions
Got a pill for all occasions

424
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:51,352
Little Sipowissot
was so nice to visit

425
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:55,075
And Scraggy Neck
is lovely to recall

426
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:58,670
I took your drug for losing weight
and now I'm a blob

427
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:01,758
But now there's so much
more of you to love

428
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:07,231
I wiped out impetigo
on the banks of Buttermilk

429
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:11,114
Flu is under firm control
in Powder Hole

430
00:36:11,240 --> 00:36:14,516
Terminus potions
tablets and lotions

431
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:17,996
Major news in modern science
Step up now and join my clients

432
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:21,556
Spent a day in Buzzard's Bay
They couldn't keep me there

433
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:24,240
Even turned away
from Kingdom Hall

434
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:26,351
They probably
threw you out

435
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:28,914
[Laughing]
They probably threw...

436
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:32,396
My hair was gray and thanks to you
it turned into pink

437
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:36,149
But that color.
It's so becoming.

438
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:40,831
- Aah!
- We're gonna wash your phony
tonics right down the sink

439
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:43,030
Wait. Listen.

440
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:46,072
My specialties are
audiology, mycology,

441
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:50,671
serology, teratology,
embryology, psychology, zoology...

442
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:53,314
and any other "ology"
you can think of!

443
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:56,512
My friends, you're not
giving me a chance!

444
00:36:56,640 --> 00:37:00,679
[Sobs] I brought all these
medicines back from Paris.

445
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:02,677
- France.
- [Crowd] Ohh!

446
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:09,519
Honi soit qui mal y pense:
Shamed be he who thinks evil of it.

447
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:13,428
And that's what the medical
business is all about, folks:
People helping people.

448
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,790
You should all have help.

449
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:18,832
Gadzooks!
What have we here?

450
00:37:18,960 --> 00:37:22,509
Oh, Doctor, Doctor, Doctor.
[Panting]

451
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:24,995
All I'm askin' for
is a miracle.

452
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:27,395
All he wants
is a miracle, folks.

453
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:32,389
How can I deny him? If he's willing
to pay for it, he's gonna get it.

454
00:37:32,520 --> 00:37:35,592
- Any price.
- One dollar, sir.

455
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:40,037
[Drumroll]

456
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:47,837
[Drumroll Ends]

457
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,555
- I trust him.
- I believe in the Doc.

458
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:10,551
I'd put my life
in his hands.

459
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:15,273
My friends you've seen a miracle
and you'll see many more

460
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:18,073
People will come pourin' in
from land and sea

461
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:21,636
We'll have centers for testing
Let's start investing

462
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:24,035
- Keep those dimes
and dollars mounting
- I'll collect

463
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:27,596
I'll do the counting
Everyone who lives here
will be strong and healthy

464
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:30,871
You'll be getting richer
by the day

465
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:36,074
- Hurray!
- Hear them acclaim us
This town will be famous

466
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:40,239
The whole wide world
will look at us and say

467
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,271
It's

468
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:51,711
Pardonmaquassy
No.

469
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:54,638
Paquamassady, no, no
Passamamassy

470
00:38:54,760 --> 00:38:57,354
Quadamapoddy
Passamadaddy

471
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:00,392
Quadampassy
Quadamaddy, Deppadaddy

472
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:03,512
Depamassy, Quadapassy
Passapassapassaquassa

473
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:07,713
- [Bawling]
- "Quoddy."

474
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:12,630
[Crowd]
Passamaquoddy

475
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:15,797
I know.

476
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:18,869
Pete, if you bring up the oil can,
we'll be ready for the night.

477
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:22,350
Sure. Before that, I'd like
to show Elliott my new suit.

478
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:26,598
No! No, no.
You can't bring Elliott up here.

479
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:30,429
Government regulation 302
states that...

480
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:32,994
no dragons
shall be allowed...

481
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,793
on the premises of
the United States' lighthouses.

482
00:39:35,920 --> 00:39:40,596
Now, go on down and get
the oil so I can mark it up
in the log that you did that.

