965
01:12:23,600 --> 01:12:27,513
Elliott went to look for Paul.
I wish he were here.

966
01:12:27,640 --> 01:12:30,200
Don't worry. They won't get you.
Come on, Dad.

967
01:12:30,320 --> 01:12:32,709
I guess we're gonna
take him back now, miss,

968
01:12:32,840 --> 01:12:35,229
to his own home, sweet home.

969
01:12:35,360 --> 01:12:39,035
- Come on, Pete.
- You won't be taking him anywhere!

970
01:12:39,160 --> 01:12:44,109
Okay, lady. We're gonna take him
whether you like it or not.

971
01:12:44,240 --> 01:12:46,674
- Right, boys?
- Right, Pa.

972
01:12:46,800 --> 01:12:49,109
Willie, you grab onto Pete,

973
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:51,151
while I hold onto her.

974
01:12:51,280 --> 01:12:54,955
You grab Pete.
I wanna hold her.

975
01:12:55,080 --> 01:12:57,594
- I wanna hold her!
- Well, I'm gonna hold her!

976
01:12:57,720 --> 01:12:59,711
[Squabbling]

977
01:12:59,840 --> 01:13:01,990
All right!

978
01:13:02,120 --> 01:13:04,839
I'll settle this.

979
01:13:04,960 --> 01:13:07,394
You two grab the brat.

980
01:13:07,520 --> 01:13:09,397
I'll hold her.

981
01:13:09,520 --> 01:13:13,638
Lf'n you think you're gonna hold her
like my boys wanna hold her,

982
01:13:13,760 --> 01:13:16,638
you're gonna be holdin' your head,
ya understand?

983
01:13:17,360 --> 01:13:19,396
Lady, that boy is ours!

984
01:13:24,200 --> 01:13:26,156
We got a bill of sale
right here

985
01:13:26,280 --> 01:13:28,555
That says
he belongs to us

986
01:13:28,680 --> 01:13:30,989
We bought him
fair and square last year

987
01:13:31,120 --> 01:13:32,997
And we own
the little cuss

988
01:13:33,120 --> 01:13:35,793
Look here
Read the writin'

989
01:13:35,920 --> 01:13:39,549
That gives us
a legal claim

990
01:13:39,680 --> 01:13:41,796
[Gogans] Oh, we got a bill
of sale right here

991
01:13:41,920 --> 01:13:44,036
With dear
little Petey's name

992
01:13:44,160 --> 01:13:47,232
- You can't have him
- He's gotta clean and sweep

993
01:13:47,360 --> 01:13:49,555
- You don't love him
- Feed the hens
and call in the sheep

994
01:13:49,680 --> 01:13:51,477
- All you've done up to now
- Plant seeds, pull weeds

995
01:13:51,600 --> 01:13:53,238
- Is break his heart
- Bow to all our needs

996
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:56,557
- You'll abuse him
- Carry water from the well

997
01:13:56,680 --> 01:13:58,875
- And just use him
- Answer every time we yell

998
01:13:59,000 --> 01:14:01,878
Watch out or I'll
take you apart

999
01:14:02,000 --> 01:14:03,956
We'd like to see you try it

1000
01:14:04,080 --> 01:14:08,119
We got a bill of sale right here
that says he belongs to us

1001
01:14:08,240 --> 01:14:13,598
Fight all you want
Won't do no good
to holler and fume and fuss

1002
01:14:13,720 --> 01:14:19,397
Leave town, keep on goin'
before I can count to five

1003
01:14:19,520 --> 01:14:22,910
- Come on! Row!
- [Explosion]

1004
01:14:23,040 --> 01:14:25,270
It's Elliott!

1005
01:14:31,640 --> 01:14:34,393
We got a bill of sale
right here

1006
01:14:34,520 --> 01:14:36,556
We got a bill of sale
right here

1007
01:14:36,680 --> 01:14:40,468
We got a bill of sale
right here

1008
01:14:40,600 --> 01:14:42,670
Right here

1009
01:14:46,080 --> 01:14:50,949
Right here

1010
01:14:53,920 --> 01:14:56,514
[Sighing]

1011
01:14:56,640 --> 01:15:00,349
It's downright dangerous,
getting all wet like this.

1012
01:15:00,480 --> 01:15:02,835
We done had
our bath in May!

1013
01:15:02,960 --> 01:15:05,520
Ahh-ahh-ahh...

1014
01:15:05,640 --> 01:15:08,552
- [Sneezing]
- [Men] Bless you, Ma.

1015
01:15:08,680 --> 01:15:11,672
- [Coughing]
- Excuse me, folks.

1016
01:15:11,800 --> 01:15:15,554
I witnessed what happened today,
and I'm completely sympathetic with you.

1017
01:15:15,680 --> 01:15:19,753
- What's sympathetic mean?
- I'm Doc Terminus. Like to talk to you.

1018
01:15:19,880 --> 01:15:22,838
Oh, Doc, I got
this here "poomonia."

1019
01:15:22,960 --> 01:15:25,633
- Sit down.
- Ahh-ahh-ahh...

1020
01:15:25,760 --> 01:15:28,797
[Sneezing]

1021
01:15:28,920 --> 01:15:30,831
- Bless you, Ma.
- Bless you, Ma.

1022
01:15:32,640 --> 01:15:36,838
[Groaning, Panting]
I got this terrible ache in my back!

1023
01:15:36,960 --> 01:15:40,270
Good. What's rightfully yours
is rightfully yours.

1024
01:15:40,400 --> 01:15:42,277
Now, you want Pete, right?

1025
01:15:42,400 --> 01:15:43,992
- Right!
- Right!
- Right!

1026
01:15:44,120 --> 01:15:46,429
I want... the dragon.

1027
01:15:46,560 --> 01:15:49,279
- The dragon?
- The dragon?
- [Laughing]

1028
01:15:55,280 --> 01:15:57,157
W-W-Wait a minute.

1029
01:15:57,280 --> 01:15:59,714
Now I got
a stitch in my side.

1030
01:15:59,840 --> 01:16:01,717
You really want
the dragon?

1031
01:16:01,840 --> 01:16:03,876
Very much. Mm-hmm.

1032
01:16:04,000 --> 01:16:06,070
Well, then, what are you willing
to give for it?

1033
01:16:06,200 --> 01:16:08,156
The help you need
getting Pete.

1034
01:16:08,280 --> 01:16:11,033
I'll need the same kind
of help getting the dragon.

1035
01:16:11,160 --> 01:16:14,277
[Cackling]

1036
01:16:15,520 --> 01:16:17,556
[Laughing]

1037
01:16:22,400 --> 01:16:25,312
N-Now I think the pain's
in my head!

1038
01:16:25,440 --> 01:16:28,557
- Have we got a deal?
- Sure.

1039
01:16:28,680 --> 01:16:32,036
We scratch your back,
you scratch ours.

1040
01:16:34,080 --> 01:16:37,550
The boathouse,
sunset, hmm?

1041
01:16:37,680 --> 01:16:39,716
Uh, Doc.

1042
01:16:39,840 --> 01:16:41,910
What you gonna do
with a dragon?

1043
01:16:42,040 --> 01:16:44,508
Oh, maybe put him on a ranch,
breed him. Hmm?

1044
01:16:44,640 --> 01:16:46,517
Big stud fees.

1045
01:17:00,400 --> 01:17:03,039
Ahoy. Ahoy. Here.

1046
01:17:06,600 --> 01:17:09,114
How would you like to make
the fishing good again?

1047
01:17:09,240 --> 01:17:12,471
- How do we do that?
- Catch that dragon!

1048
01:17:12,600 --> 01:17:16,070
Set a trap for him, throw a net
over him, drag him away.

1049
01:17:16,200 --> 01:17:19,556
Good-bye, Elliott.
Hello, fish. Hmm?

1050
01:17:19,680 --> 01:17:22,592
Sunset, the boathouse.
Spread the word, hmm?

1051
01:17:25,840 --> 01:17:29,833
[Fishermen Murmuring
In Agreement]

1052
01:17:50,800 --> 01:17:52,791
Get back!
Get back!

1053
01:17:58,120 --> 01:18:01,908
Dr. Terminus! Here's that
there harpoon you wanted!

1054
01:18:02,040 --> 01:18:04,349
Good! Put it
right over there!

1055
01:18:05,960 --> 01:18:07,996
[Ma]
Now you just remember our bargain!

1056
01:18:09,680 --> 01:18:13,116
Okay, I want separate trip lines
on the primary tarp,

1057
01:18:13,240 --> 01:18:15,800
the secondary net
and on the tertiary.

1058
01:18:15,920 --> 01:18:18,354
- T-Tertiary?
- What's that?

1059
01:18:18,480 --> 01:18:22,314
Dragon medicine.
[Cackling]

1060
01:18:22,440 --> 01:18:24,556
- Okay, fix it.
- We've done it!

1061
01:18:24,680 --> 01:18:26,716
Don't signal
till you're re...

1062
01:18:26,840 --> 01:18:30,833
- [Men Shouting]
- Get this net up off of me!

1063
01:18:30,960 --> 01:18:35,112
Will you get this... Will you
get this net up! Up! Up!

1064
01:18:35,240 --> 01:18:37,117
Now, I've gotta go
and get that kid.

1065
01:18:37,240 --> 01:18:39,834
You rehearse this and make it run
like clockwork or else.

1066
01:18:59,080 --> 01:19:00,957
Elliott!

1067
01:19:04,480 --> 01:19:07,756
Oh, Elliott, you were terrific
the way you saved us from the Gogans.

1068
01:19:07,880 --> 01:19:10,155
- [Laughing]
- What?

1069
01:19:10,280 --> 01:19:14,512
[Gibberish]

1070
01:19:14,640 --> 01:19:16,471
Do you mean it?

1071
01:19:16,600 --> 01:19:18,477
[Clicking Tongue]

1072
01:19:18,600 --> 01:19:20,636
Wow! That's great.

1073
01:19:20,760 --> 01:19:23,399
You're the most wonderful dragon
in the whole world.

1074
01:19:23,520 --> 01:19:26,193
[Soft Growling,
Clicking Tongue]

1075
01:19:26,320 --> 01:19:28,276
Wait till I tell Nora!

1076
01:19:29,760 --> 01:19:33,275
[Humming]

1077
01:19:34,960 --> 01:19:37,155
Nora! Nora! Good news!

1078
01:19:37,280 --> 01:19:40,078
Elliott found Paul,
and he's on his way home!

1079
01:19:42,440 --> 01:19:45,034
- Pete...
- I wouldn't say anything
like that if I were you.

1080
01:19:45,160 --> 01:19:48,311
But it's true.
Elliott said.

1081
01:19:48,440 --> 01:19:51,034
Please.

1082
01:19:51,160 --> 01:19:53,549
There's been enough talk
about Paul,

1083
01:19:53,680 --> 01:19:56,148
and Elliott too.

1084
01:19:56,280 --> 01:19:59,033
[Sighing]
Both of us have to be...

1085
01:20:00,240 --> 01:20:02,117
realistic.

1086
01:20:02,240 --> 01:20:07,030
Paul's ship went down.
He's not coming back.

1087
01:20:07,160 --> 01:20:10,311
And I have to adjust
my life to it.

1088
01:20:10,440 --> 01:20:12,954
You have to make
a big adjustment too.

1089
01:20:14,160 --> 01:20:16,435
You have us now.

1090
01:20:16,560 --> 01:20:19,791
You don't have to make believe
your only friend is a dragon.

1091
01:20:19,920 --> 01:20:22,434
But I'm not making believe.

1092
01:20:22,560 --> 01:20:24,835
That's what I mean
by "realistic."

1093
01:20:24,960 --> 01:20:27,554
There are no dragons.

1094
01:20:27,680 --> 01:20:30,672
Except for Elliott.
He's real.

1095
01:20:30,800 --> 01:20:32,711
Lampie, you've seen him,
haven't you?

1096
01:20:37,760 --> 01:20:39,716
Well, l...

1097
01:20:42,080 --> 01:20:43,991
I thought I saw him.

1098
01:20:47,960 --> 01:20:52,670
Wait till Paul gets here. Then you'll
know how realistic Elliott is.

1099
01:20:54,440 --> 01:20:56,317
Okay.

1100
01:20:56,440 --> 01:21:00,319
Until that time, let's try
not to talk about it.

1101
01:21:02,640 --> 01:21:04,915
How about filling
the reserve oil can?

1102
01:21:05,040 --> 01:21:06,837
Sure.

1103
01:21:10,920 --> 01:21:13,832
Well, at least one of us
is entitled to have illusions.

1104
01:21:18,120 --> 01:21:21,795
[Thunderclap]

1105
01:21:24,560 --> 01:21:27,472
[Wind Howling]

1106
01:21:27,600 --> 01:21:29,477
Pete! Pete, it's Elliott!

1107
01:21:29,600 --> 01:21:32,194
- What's the matter?
- Elliott's in Passapaka... Pakadaka...

1108
01:21:32,320 --> 01:21:34,436
He's in town, and he's
tearing the place apart.

1109
01:21:34,560 --> 01:21:36,437
- You've gotta do something.
- Oh, no!

1110
01:21:38,440 --> 01:21:40,351
[Laughing]

1111
01:21:52,040 --> 01:21:54,838
We should be
in the channel.

1112
01:21:54,960 --> 01:21:57,793
We should've made
Passamaquoddy Light by now.

1113
01:21:57,920 --> 01:22:01,435
I know the light keepers
personally.

1114
01:22:01,560 --> 01:22:05,109
- He's in there! Come on!
- Elliott! Elliott!

1115
01:22:07,480 --> 01:22:10,119
Did I say the primary
was really the tertiary?

1116
01:22:10,240 --> 01:22:13,118
[Men Shouting]

1117
01:22:13,240 --> 01:22:15,310
Never!

1118
01:22:18,520 --> 01:22:21,318
- Where's Elliott?
- Nowhere!

1119
01:22:21,440 --> 01:22:25,069
Your hokey-pokey dragon's
out helping Santa Claus pull his sled!

1120
01:22:25,200 --> 01:22:27,191
- Boys!
- Let me go!

1121
01:22:27,320 --> 01:22:29,356
Now you're never
gonna get away again!

1122
01:22:29,480 --> 01:22:31,550
We're gonna put chains
on you when you're workin'!

1123
01:22:31,680 --> 01:22:33,796
- And when you're not workin'.
- And when you're sleepin'!

1124
01:22:33,920 --> 01:22:36,639
Okay, okay. Tear him to pieces
in your own time.

1125
01:22:36,760 --> 01:22:38,796
Right now he is
the bait for the trap.

1126
01:22:38,920 --> 01:22:41,480
Take him in there where that thing can
see him when he comes through the door.

1127
01:22:41,600 --> 01:22:44,068
He'll head straight for Pete.
We spring the trap.

1128
01:22:44,200 --> 01:22:47,237
After the tertiary net drops on him,
I'll give you the signal,

1129
01:22:47,360 --> 01:22:50,033
and you fire the harpoon
right into the middle.

1130
01:22:50,160 --> 01:22:54,233
- No! No!
- Yes! Yes! Got it?

1131
01:22:54,360 --> 01:22:56,396
Got it!

1132
01:22:56,520 --> 01:23:00,274
But what I don't got is,
h-h-how you gonna get that monster,

1133
01:23:00,400 --> 01:23:05,349
that hideous beast, that nightmare
sent by the devil, to come here?

1134
01:23:05,480 --> 01:23:09,758
Easy. We get someone he knows
to bring him here.

1135
01:23:09,880 --> 01:23:12,030
Well, who'd be crazy enough
to do that?

1136
01:23:13,440 --> 01:23:16,477
No! No!

1137
01:23:16,600 --> 01:23:19,831
He knows you.
He trusts you.

1138
01:23:19,960 --> 01:23:23,919
He scares me!
He hates me!

1139
01:23:25,240 --> 01:23:27,151
Hoagy.

1140
01:23:27,280 --> 01:23:30,158
We are all on this earth
for a purpose,

1141
01:23:30,280 --> 01:23:33,431
and the time
for your purpose is now.

1142
01:23:33,560 --> 01:23:37,712
I know that inside this pale, frail,
pathetic shell of a man...

1143
01:23:37,840 --> 01:23:40,798
there is a Vesuvius
ready to erupt.

1144
01:23:40,920 --> 01:23:43,036
Now, I've known you,
man and beast,

1145
01:23:43,160 --> 01:23:45,390
since, since you
were nothing.

1146
01:23:45,520 --> 01:23:51,072
But now, Hoagy, now,
you're still nothing,

1147
01:23:51,200 --> 01:23:53,760
but you could be
something!

1148
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:56,155
You can be a somebody.

1149
01:23:56,280 --> 01:24:01,559
A legend, Hoagy. A legend in
your own lifetime, not a joke!

1150
01:24:01,680 --> 01:24:04,035
The moment's here, Hoagy.

1151
01:24:04,160 --> 01:24:06,037
Grab it. Grab it!

1152
01:24:06,160 --> 01:24:10,915
Today the jester.
Tomorrow the king!

1153
01:24:15,240 --> 01:24:17,708
- No!
- Get out!

1154
01:24:20,240 --> 01:24:22,276
[Whimpering]

1155
01:24:34,920 --> 01:24:36,876
[Elliott Snoring]

1156
01:24:37,000 --> 01:24:39,389
E-Elliott.

1157
01:24:39,520 --> 01:24:42,796
C-Can you come out here
for a second? Please?

1158
01:24:45,600 --> 01:24:47,989
[Snoring]

1159
01:24:48,120 --> 01:24:50,429
[Gasping]

1160
01:24:50,560 --> 01:24:52,755
[Snoring]

1161
01:24:55,480 --> 01:24:58,358
[Snoring]

1162
01:25:05,320 --> 01:25:07,197
Wake up.

1163
01:25:07,320 --> 01:25:09,276
W-W-Wake up!

1164
01:25:09,400 --> 01:25:12,039
[Snarling]

1165
01:25:12,160 --> 01:25:16,676
D-D-Don't get n-n-nervous!

1166
01:25:16,800 --> 01:25:18,677
I'm a friend.

1167
01:25:18,800 --> 01:25:20,631
[Groaning, Snorting]

1168
01:25:20,760 --> 01:25:23,832
Don't roast me!

1169
01:25:23,960 --> 01:25:26,997
[Snarling]
Boo!

1170
01:25:27,120 --> 01:25:30,351
- Ahh!
- [Laughing]

1171
01:25:32,200 --> 01:25:34,475
H-Hon... Honest.

1172
01:25:34,600 --> 01:25:36,636
L-l-I-I-I got a m-mess...

1173
01:25:36,760 --> 01:25:40,719
m-m-m-message about P-P-Pete!

1174
01:25:42,120 --> 01:25:46,477
- T-The G-G-Gogans...
- [Snarling]

1175
01:25:46,600 --> 01:25:49,592
Got P-P-P-Pete!

1176
01:25:49,720 --> 01:25:52,757
- [Bellowing]
- Ahh!

1177
01:25:52,880 --> 01:25:55,633
[Snarling, Roaring]

1178
01:25:55,760 --> 01:25:58,991
Aaah!

1179
01:26:03,920 --> 01:26:05,751
Follow me!

1180
01:26:25,200 --> 01:26:27,430
[Thunderclap]

1181
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:31,998
There's a reef between us
and the channel.

1182
01:26:32,120 --> 01:26:34,190
Dad, I can't find Pete.

1183
01:26:36,200 --> 01:26:39,556
- Can you get it lit?
- I have to put in a dry wick.

1184
01:26:41,720 --> 01:26:43,597
Battle stations!

1185
01:26:46,520 --> 01:26:48,875
[Hoagy] I told you!
I told you, Elliott! There he is!

1186
01:26:49,000 --> 01:26:51,195
Look out, Elliott!
It's a trap!

1187
01:26:51,320 --> 01:26:53,754
Aaah! Get him!
He's right here!

1188
01:26:55,040 --> 01:26:57,190
Drop everything!

1189
01:26:58,840 --> 01:27:00,876
Drop everything!

1190
01:27:01,000 --> 01:27:03,230
[Men Shouting]

1191
01:27:03,360 --> 01:27:06,193
[Elliott Bellowing]

1192
01:27:06,320 --> 01:27:08,754
Elliott, over here!

1193
01:27:08,880 --> 01:27:13,078
[Hoagy] Get me out of here!
Elliott, don't step on me!

1194
01:27:15,360 --> 01:27:19,956
- Am I seeing what I think I'm seeing?
- It's beginnin' to look like a...

1195
01:27:20,080 --> 01:27:21,957
- Dragon!
- Don't say that!

1196
01:27:22,080 --> 01:27:25,311
I've got it!
We've done it! Out!

1197
01:27:25,440 --> 01:27:27,556
We've got it!
We've got it!

1198
01:27:27,680 --> 01:27:29,557
- Hoagy!
- [Elliott Growling]

1199
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:31,557
Please!
Please, let me out!

1200
01:27:31,680 --> 01:27:35,309
- Doc, please!
- Get out of there! Get out of there!

1201
01:27:35,440 --> 01:27:39,433
- Doc, get me out!
Get me out! Get me out!
- Okay. Okay!

1202
01:27:39,560 --> 01:27:43,838
[Growling]

1203
01:27:43,960 --> 01:27:47,714
- [Growling]
- [Men Shouting]

1204
01:27:49,200 --> 01:27:52,112
Help, Elliott, help!

1205
01:27:54,000 --> 01:27:57,072
Man this harpoon. Take this.
[Chuckling]

1206
01:27:59,000 --> 01:28:01,753
Light the fuse.

1207
01:28:01,880 --> 01:28:05,031
No, no!
Don't shoot Elliott!

1208
01:28:05,160 --> 01:28:07,754
[Ma Screaming,
Shouting]

1209
01:28:07,880 --> 01:28:13,159
[Pa]
Get him back! Get him back!

1210
01:28:13,280 --> 01:28:15,271
The other.

1211
01:28:18,960 --> 01:28:22,270
- [Pa] Pick him up!
- [Ma] Take him outside!

1212
01:28:25,400 --> 01:28:28,198
[Hoagy]
Get out of the way!

1213
01:28:28,320 --> 01:28:30,390
- [Whimpering]
- [Screaming]

1214
01:28:30,520 --> 01:28:32,750
He's going!
Let me get a bead on him!

1215
01:28:35,760 --> 01:28:39,799
- Elliott, save me!
- [Ma] Don't let him get away again!
Get him outta here!

1216
01:28:48,480 --> 01:28:51,677
- Hands...
- Elliott, don't let 'em take me!

1217
01:28:51,800 --> 01:28:54,553
[Growling]

1218
01:28:59,320 --> 01:29:01,356
[Roaring]

1219
01:29:03,160 --> 01:29:05,549
[Stammering]
Wait! Wait!

1220
01:29:05,680 --> 01:29:08,114
[Ma Shouting]

1221
01:29:18,480 --> 01:29:21,119
- [Muttering]
- [Gogans Whimpering]

1222
01:29:21,240 --> 01:29:23,117
Huh? Pete!

1223
01:29:26,440 --> 01:29:28,749
- Thanks, Elliott.
- [Muttering]

1224
01:29:28,880 --> 01:29:31,599
You just listen to me!
That there boy belongs to me!

1225
01:29:31,720 --> 01:29:37,590
I paid fifty dollars for him,
plus legals, and I got a bill
of sale right here to prove it.

1226
01:29:47,520 --> 01:29:49,476
[Snarling]

1227
01:29:50,680 --> 01:29:53,274
- Boo.
- [Screaming]

1228
01:29:53,400 --> 01:29:56,790
[Ma]
Merle, help! Don't just stand there!

1229
01:29:56,920 --> 01:30:01,072
Come on! Get me outta here!
Get me outta here!

1230
01:30:01,200 --> 01:30:02,679
[Ma]
You clucks!

1231
01:30:02,800 --> 01:30:06,713
[Elliott Laughing]

1232
01:30:10,240 --> 01:30:13,437
- [Grunting, Groaning]
- [Ma] Let him keep the brat!

1233
01:30:13,560 --> 01:30:15,437
[Roaring]

1234
01:30:15,560 --> 01:30:18,233
[Ma]
Come on! Get in the wagon!

1235
01:30:18,360 --> 01:30:20,669
[Shouting]

1236
01:30:20,800 --> 01:30:23,758
[Ma]
Wait! Wait for us!

1237
01:30:35,920 --> 01:30:38,115
[Elliott Howling]

1238
01:30:54,760 --> 01:30:56,318
Daaah-ah-ah!

1239
01:31:00,480 --> 01:31:03,278
Aaah-hoo-hoo-hoo!
[Screaming]

1240
01:31:03,400 --> 01:31:07,313
Aaah! Doh!

1241
01:31:11,200 --> 01:31:13,873
Hoagy, get me down!

1242
01:31:14,000 --> 01:31:17,436
We've gotta do something!
That dragon's gonna get away!

1243
01:31:17,560 --> 01:31:19,994
[Snarling]

1244
01:31:20,120 --> 01:31:23,908
[Screaming]
He's gonna eat us up!

1245
01:31:24,040 --> 01:31:27,430
[Growling]

1246
01:31:27,560 --> 01:31:29,516
Oh!

1247
01:31:29,640 --> 01:31:33,519
[Whimpering]

1248
01:31:38,480 --> 01:31:41,597
[Wagon Crashing]

1249
01:31:43,120 --> 01:31:46,192
...in the street.
Quite a storm here.

1250
01:31:46,320 --> 01:31:48,914
Wait a minute.
Watch those stairs.

1251
01:31:50,320 --> 01:31:54,199
- [Gasping]
- [Electricity Crackling]

1252
01:31:54,320 --> 01:31:56,117
Oh, look!

1253
01:32:06,560 --> 01:32:08,516
Th-Th-There really
is a dragon!

1254
01:32:08,640 --> 01:32:10,756
Yes, and he saved us!

1255
01:32:10,880 --> 01:32:13,269
- Dragon!
- A dragon! A real dragon!

1256
01:32:14,560 --> 01:32:17,552
- Attaboy, Elliott.
- [Muttering]

1257
01:32:17,680 --> 01:32:20,877
[Clicking Tongue]

1258
01:32:25,720 --> 01:32:27,358
That ship's headed
for the reef!

1259
01:32:27,480 --> 01:32:29,471
Go down and sound
the foghorn!

1260
01:32:34,680 --> 01:32:37,399
[Foghorn Blowing]

1261
01:32:37,520 --> 01:32:40,239
Elliott, quick! Quick!

1262
01:32:50,920 --> 01:32:54,629
[Foghorn Blowing]

1263
01:32:56,200 --> 01:32:58,919
[Ship Creaking]

1264
01:33:02,320 --> 01:33:05,312
Nora, let me have the light
so I can see what I'm doing.

1265
01:33:07,640 --> 01:33:09,631
[Foghorn Blowing]

1266
01:33:19,240 --> 01:33:22,232
Come on, Elliott.
You can do it.

1267
01:33:24,960 --> 01:33:27,872
- [Foghorn Blowing]
- I got it!

1268
01:33:32,320 --> 01:33:34,197
Come on, Elliott.

1269
01:33:41,200 --> 01:33:44,317
- [Foghorn Blowing]
- Come on, Elliott!

1270
01:33:44,440 --> 01:33:47,113
[Panting]

1271
01:33:47,240 --> 01:33:49,151
[Pete]
Hurry!

1272
01:33:49,280 --> 01:33:51,475
What's the matter?

1273
01:33:51,600 --> 01:33:54,239
Everything is wet in here,
that's what's the matter!

1274
01:33:54,360 --> 01:33:57,591
- Don't worry, Lampie. Elliott came.
- Elliott?

1275
01:33:57,720 --> 01:34:01,918
That's all I need is
a dragon in here. Ah!

1276
01:34:02,040 --> 01:34:03,917
Get him outta here!

1277
01:34:04,040 --> 01:34:05,792
[Muttering]

1278
01:34:05,920 --> 01:34:08,354
Start your burner, Elliott.
Light the wick.

1279
01:34:08,480 --> 01:34:10,675
[Gibberish]

1280
01:34:10,800 --> 01:34:15,396
- [Clicking Tongue]
- All right, Elliott. Go ahead. Light it.

1281
01:34:20,040 --> 01:34:22,679
[Pete]
Now, Elliott! Now!

1282
01:34:22,800 --> 01:34:24,950
All right.
Where's the fire?

1283
01:34:25,080 --> 01:34:27,036
- [Groaning]
- What's the matter?

1284
01:34:27,160 --> 01:34:31,358
[Gibberish, Sputtering]

1285
01:34:31,480 --> 01:34:34,358
- He's all squished up in the stairs.
- [Foghorn Blowing]

1286
01:34:47,640 --> 01:34:50,712
- [Foghorn Blowing]
- [Elliott Blowing]

1287
01:34:54,040 --> 01:34:57,510
- El-Elliott?
- [Gibberish]

1288
01:34:57,640 --> 01:35:00,154
He's real.
He's really real.

1289
01:35:00,280 --> 01:35:02,396
[Muttering,
Clicking Tongue]

1290
01:35:02,520 --> 01:35:05,717
- Of course he is.
He's gonna light the wick.
- Can he do it?

1291
01:35:05,840 --> 01:35:09,230
Can he? He can throw a flame clear
across to Bar Harbor...

1292
01:35:09,360 --> 01:35:12,750
if he can get
his own burner goin'!

1293
01:35:14,160 --> 01:35:16,196
[Gasping]

1294
01:35:19,360 --> 01:35:22,193
- Come on, Elliott!
- [Whining]
- Go on!

1295
01:35:22,320 --> 01:35:23,992
[Lampie]
Blow, Elliott!

1296
01:35:28,360 --> 01:35:32,717
[Drawing A Deep Breath]

1297
01:35:36,320 --> 01:35:39,517
- Wow! [Panting]
- [Pete] Elliott, you did it!

1298
01:35:41,320 --> 01:35:46,155
[Gibberish,
Clicking Tongue]

1299
01:35:46,280 --> 01:35:48,714
Look there!

1300
01:35:50,640 --> 01:35:53,473
That means the harbor
is dead ahead, Captain!

1301
01:35:56,560 --> 01:35:58,516
Hard right rudder!

1302
01:36:08,320 --> 01:36:12,836
Elliott, I could give you
a great big kiss.

1303
01:36:29,080 --> 01:36:30,911
[Shuddering]

1304
01:36:34,920 --> 01:36:37,992
A dragon, a dragon
You bet we saw a dragon

1305
01:36:38,120 --> 01:36:41,476
So big and brave, he came to
save a village in distress

1306
01:36:41,600 --> 01:36:44,990
He kept the ship from crashing
when he heard the S.O.S.

1307
01:36:45,120 --> 01:36:48,078
He faced a group of villains
and he fought them with success

1308
01:36:48,200 --> 01:36:50,077
He's great
He's great

1309
01:36:50,200 --> 01:36:52,031
- A chum
- A pal
- A mate

1310
01:36:52,160 --> 01:36:55,436
A dragon, a dragon
We're proud to love a dragon

1311
01:36:55,560 --> 01:36:59,075
Before he came to fight the storm
the night was dark and dim

1312
01:36:59,200 --> 01:37:02,590
Now everyone in town is safe again
because of him

1313
01:37:02,720 --> 01:37:05,757
He filled the ocean full of fish
He packed it to the brim

1314
01:37:05,880 --> 01:37:09,190
We want it known
that he's our very own

1315
01:37:09,320 --> 01:37:13,279
Nora! Nora!

1316
01:37:15,800 --> 01:37:17,995
Paul!

1317
01:37:27,200 --> 01:37:30,351
Gather around, everyone. I'm going
to have a few appropriate words to say.

1318
01:37:30,480 --> 01:37:32,789
Gather around. Come on.
Closer, closer.

1319
01:37:32,920 --> 01:37:35,832
There you are, yes.
It's nice to see you.

1320
01:37:35,960 --> 01:37:39,475
Ladies...
Ladies and gentlemen,

1321
01:37:39,600 --> 01:37:42,478
Pete, I want you to thank
Elliott the dragon...

1322
01:37:42,600 --> 01:37:44,477
for the council here
and all the townspeople.

1323
01:37:44,600 --> 01:37:47,273
- You do that?
- Well, he's right here.

1324
01:37:47,400 --> 01:37:50,073
He'd appreciate it
if you'd thank him yourself.

1325
01:37:50,200 --> 01:37:53,715
- [Laughter]
- You mean I can talk right to him, huh?

1326
01:37:53,840 --> 01:37:58,118
Go right to the main source.
That was my campaign...

1327
01:37:58,240 --> 01:38:00,595
- No, he's over here.
- Oh! Oh, over that side.

1328
01:38:00,720 --> 01:38:03,280
So, uh, on behalf of...

1329
01:38:03,400 --> 01:38:06,073
[Laughter]

1330
01:38:06,200 --> 01:38:08,760
[Muttering]
Thank you.

1331
01:38:08,880 --> 01:38:11,792
It's a brazzle dazzle day

1332
01:38:11,920 --> 01:38:15,595
- So throw off the past
and everything in it
- [Elliott Clicking Tongue]

1333
01:38:15,720 --> 01:38:18,359
That's the brazzle
dazzle way

1334
01:38:18,480 --> 01:38:21,438
Enjoying your time
from minute to minute

1335
01:38:23,360 --> 01:38:25,590
Hi!

1336
01:38:26,920 --> 01:38:29,229
Oh, Elliott,
you're the greatest.

1337
01:38:29,360 --> 01:38:32,796
You've made everybody happy,
especially me.

1338
01:38:32,920 --> 01:38:35,480
I'm very proud of you.

1339
01:38:35,600 --> 01:38:37,750
[Muttering]

1340
01:38:37,880 --> 01:38:41,919
We've got a real family now
and a place to live.

1341
01:38:43,560 --> 01:38:45,437
[Clearing Throat]

1342
01:38:45,560 --> 01:38:50,634
[Gibberish]

1343
01:38:50,760 --> 01:38:54,878
You've gotta go?
When will you be back?

1344
01:38:56,480 --> 01:38:59,870
[Gulping, Muttering,
Sniffling]

1345
01:39:05,320 --> 01:39:08,312
You... You won't be back?

1346
01:39:08,440 --> 01:39:12,069
[Muttering]

1347
01:39:12,200 --> 01:39:14,873
But why?

1348
01:39:15,000 --> 01:39:17,434
Did I do something wrong?

1349
01:39:17,560 --> 01:39:20,028
[Muttering]

1350
01:39:21,160 --> 01:39:23,037
[Snarling]

1351
01:39:25,160 --> 01:39:27,116
There's another kid
in trouble?

1352
01:39:27,240 --> 01:39:30,437
[Muttering,
Growling]

1353
01:39:30,560 --> 01:39:32,437
[Soft Roar]

1354
01:39:33,960 --> 01:39:36,872
Well, if anyone can get him
out of it, you can.

1355
01:39:37,000 --> 01:39:39,798
- Ohh...
- [Giggling]

1356
01:39:43,200 --> 01:39:45,794
[Muttering]

1357
01:39:45,920 --> 01:39:49,435
I won't see you again,
will I?

1358
01:39:51,160 --> 01:39:53,276
Ever.

1359
01:39:53,400 --> 01:39:55,197
[Sniffling, Whimpering]

1360
01:39:59,680 --> 01:40:01,750
[Sniffling]

1361
01:40:01,880 --> 01:40:03,757
What are you sniffing for?

1362
01:40:06,240 --> 01:40:08,231
[Gasping, Sneezing]

1363
01:40:08,360 --> 01:40:10,430
[Laughing]

1364
01:40:10,560 --> 01:40:13,950
[Chuckling]

1365
01:40:14,080 --> 01:40:16,878
Now, remember,
don't scare people.

1366
01:40:17,000 --> 01:40:19,753
[Gibberish]

1367
01:40:32,360 --> 01:40:34,510
Good-bye, Elliott.
Good-bye.

1368
01:40:37,760 --> 01:40:39,716
[Gibberish]

1369
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:56,229
- It is a dragon!
- [Pete, Lampie, Nora] It's Elliott!

1370
01:40:58,120 --> 01:41:00,998
[Pete] And remember,
you're supposed to be invisible!

